Haco Industries has begun donating sanitisers to vulnerable communities, hospitals and county governments to keep communities safe from the coronavirus. The donations took place in different places around the city, among them Amref Health Africa, Pumwani Maternity, Loresho phandwasholice, Don Bosco church and Red Cross. Haco Industries also launched Amara antibacterial handwash and Ace surface disinfectant to provide a holistic solution for homes and institutions.